<br>
It's always a good idea to try to work a background into the piece before going to CG. Whether or not you use the lines from it depends on what you want it to look like.<br>
<br>
There's really no set of rules that I know of. Some people like Shousetsu can whip up an amazing background in Photoshop alone, but I prefer to do most if it in ink before CGing. It's mainly stylistic, but admitted, different approaches fit better with different pictures. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/shellt.gif"> <a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/gallery/main.html">Spike the Tortoise</a><BR>
